description:
&lt;p&gt;Northampton General Hospital NHS Trust is going through a major re-organisation within our Estates Department making this an exciting period of change and development to support delivery of our vision and strategic objectives. As a department we are making major investments in our infrastructure with the investment and development of our existing engineering maintenance team together with the introduction of new staff and roles.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for experienced dynamic individuals to join NGH as Estates Engineering Technicians within the operational estates team, with Electrical or Mechanical qualifications and or extensive experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers an excellent opportunity for an innovative engineer to influence and play a key role in the engineering estate. You will be expected to work closely with a wide range of staff from different disciplines including Clinicians and Design Consultants to assist in the delivery of schemes to support a high standard of patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be self-motivated, well organised and enthusiastic with excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are qualified or highly experienced within the Electrical or Mechanical discipline or have experience of working with complex building systems within the National Health Service or public sector or have experience of working within a busy environment to strict deadlines, then this is a for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time and Part Time applicants welcome.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: James Stewart Job title: Business &amp; Compliance Manager Email address: james.stewart@ngh.nhs.uk Telephone number: 01604 545087&lt;/p&gt;
